The paper deals with information theory and coding for data structures, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of Galton-Watson trees and random graphs suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The focus on large deviation principles suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
